summary: What order should I watch the marvel movies?
body:
What order should I watch the marvel movies?

Since Endgame came out, I’ve decided to watch the other Marvel movies (I’ve never seen them before) and then watch it at the cinema. I searched it online, and apparently Captain America: the first Avenger is the first one you should watch. I’ve just finished watching it but from here on people have different opinions: some say that you should now watch Captain Marvel, since that is the chronological order in the MCU, but others say that you should watch them in the order that they were released.

Can someone who’s seen the movies help me out? I think I should watch them in the order that they were released but I think a fan’s opinion would be useful.

summary: We need to talk about how awesome Carol was in Avengers Endgame. How she rescues Tony and Nebula from space. How her first...
body:
We need to talk about how awesome Carol was in Avengers Endgame.

How she rescues Tony and Nebula from space.

How her first thought after finding out about the Snape was track down and kill Thanos.

How she didn’t take the crap Rhodey gave that he gave her about her absence lying down, since she had other planets to protect.

How she didn’t even flinch when Thor purposely summoned Stormbreaker to see if she’d get rattled.

How she stayed proactive during those five years trying to help other planets recover from The Snap, but still stayed in contact with the Avengers on Earth.

How awesome she looked with her shorter haircut.

How she single-handedly decimated Thanos’ ship.

How Thanos head butted her and she didn’t even flinch.

Carol is the Captain we deserve.

summary: About Avengers:Endgame
body:
About Avengers:Endgame

Spoiler ahead!

Why we didn’t get a hug or even a nod scene of Fury and Carol?

I mean, we had the scene of her all emotional over his “missing” picture!

I know that Carol is only a tiny character for this movie - I understand, she’s not supposed to be the center or even get more attention than the old kids/Avengers. I’m not asking a whole scene like Scott Lang had looking for his kid or 2min of it…

I’m just pissed to not see a simple nod between friends, Nick and Carol deserved 5seconds!!!!

Not fair.
